snippet.textDisplay: Does tumbleweed make good kindling, or at least a good fire starter? If so then some enterprising person might want to collect them and put them through a baling machine to make them into something resembling bales of straw. Or maybe make compost out of them. With their thorns they might even be made into a kind of biodegradable barrier, and perhaps even woven into matting, especially if you find some way of removing the thorns. And if the woody material they are made of is suitable, even use them as a form of cheap insulation in buildings (having treated them first with a fireproofing agent.
